<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>DIY Claude Code Personal Assistant Setup | Built with Jon</title>
  <meta name="description" content="A technical DIY setup checklist for building a file-based AI personal assistant with Claude Code, a local resource pack, Google context, and safe approval boundaries.">
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after {
      box-sizing: border-box;
      margin: 0;
    }

    :root {
      --font-body: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, sans-serif;
      --font-mono: "SF Mono", "Fira Code", "Fira Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
      --color-bg: #fbf6ec;
      --color-text: #1f1713;
      --color-text-muted: #5e5047;
      --color-accent: #3b6e8f;
      --color-accent-hover: #1d4ed8;
      --color-border: #e5d7c3;
      --color-surface: #fffdf8;
      --color-code-bg: #f2e7d6;
      --color-jules-orange: #e8752b;
      --color-copper: #8f4e24;
      --color-sage: #6e8b6f;
      --color-plum: #7a4e68;
      --shadow-soft: 0 8px 22px rgba(31, 23, 19, 0.08);
      --shadow-card: 0 16px 42px rgba(31, 23, 19, 0.1);
      --max-width: 920px;
    }

    html {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    body {
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 0 1.5rem 4rem;
      color: var(--color-text);
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 18% 8%, rgba(255, 253, 248, 0.78), transparent 34%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-bg) 0%, #f7efe2 100%);
    }

    a {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      color: var(--color-accent-hover);
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    a:focus-visible {
      outline: 3px solid var(--color-jules-orange);
      outline-offset: 4px;
      border-radius: 6px;
    }

    summary:focus-visible {
      outline: 3px solid var(--color-jules-orange);
      outline-offset: -6px;
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    .page {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: var(--max-width);
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .site-header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      padding: 1.5rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      background: rgba(251, 246, 236, 0.8);
    }

    .site-name {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    .top-link {
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      font-weight: 650;
    }

    .top-link:first-of-type {
      margin-left: auto;
    }

    .hero-actions {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.7rem;
      margin-top: 1.2rem;
    }

    .hero-action {
      display: inline-flex;
      min-height: 44px;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 0.65rem 0.9rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: var(--color-surface);
      color: var(--color-text);
      font-weight: 720;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .hero-action.primary {
      border-color: var(--color-accent);
      background: var(--color-accent);
      color: #fff;
    }

    .hero-action:hover {
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .hero {
      max-width: 760px;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .eyebrow,
    .section-label,
    .step-label,
    .pill {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 750;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      line-height: 1.2;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      color: var(--color-copper);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    h1,
    h2,
    h3 {
      line-height: 1.3;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    h1 {
      max-width: 700px;
      margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .lede {
      max-width: 650px;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .panel {
      background: rgba(255, 253, 248, 0.94);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
    }

    .bring-panel {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      padding: 1.35rem;
      border-left: 7px solid var(--color-jules-orange);
    }

    .bring-panel h2 {
      margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }

    .bring-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }

    .bring-list li {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto minmax(0, 1fr);
      gap: 0.65rem;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }

    .safety-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.65rem;
      padding-left: 1.15rem;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }

    .check {
      display: inline-grid;
      width: 1.35rem;
      height: 1.35rem;
      place-items: center;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: var(--color-accent);
      color: #fff;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      line-height: 1;
    }

    .section-label {
      margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }

    .setup-stack {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.8rem;
    }

    details {
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    summary {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) auto;
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      list-style: none;
    }

    summary::-webkit-details-marker {
      display: none;
    }

    .step-label {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
      color: var(--color-accent);
    }

    .summary-desc {
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
      margin-bottom: 0;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }

    .chevron {
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      transition: transform 0.18s ease;
    }

    details[open] > summary .chevron {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    .detail-body {
      padding: 0 1.3rem 1.35rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .detail-body > *:first-child {
      margin-top: 1.1rem;
    }

    .detail-body h3 {
      margin: 1.2rem 0 0.55rem;
    }

    .detail-body h3:first-child {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-callout {
      margin: 1rem 0;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(143, 78, 36, 0.24);
      border-left: 5px solid #d19a22;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: rgba(245, 197, 66, 0.16);
    }

    .privacy-heading {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.65rem;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    }

    .privacy-heading h3 {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .caution-icon {
      position: relative;
      display: inline-block;
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      width: 1.55rem;
      height: 1.35rem;
    }

    .caution-icon::before {
      position: absolute;
      top: 0.05rem;
      left: 0;
      content: "";
      border-right: 0.775rem solid transparent;
      border-bottom: 1.35rem solid #f5c542;
      border-left: 0.775rem solid transparent;
    }

    .caution-icon span {
      position: absolute;
      top: 0.42rem;
      left: 0;
      width: 1.55rem;
      color: var(--color-text);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 900;
      line-height: 1;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .step-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.85rem;
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
    }

    .step-list li {
      padding-left: 0.15rem;
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }

    .step-list strong,
    .bring-list strong,
    .safety-list strong {
      color: var(--color-text);
    }

    code {
      padding: 0.08rem 0.3rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      background: var(--color-code-bg);
      color: var(--color-text);
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.84em;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .note {
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 0.95rem 1rem;
      border-left: 5px solid var(--color-accent);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: rgba(59, 110, 143, 0.08);
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .provider-options {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.7rem;
      margin-top: 1.1rem;
    }

    .provider-card {
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: rgba(251, 246, 236, 0.52);
      box-shadow: none;
    }

    .provider-card summary {
      padding: 0.95rem 1rem;
    }

    .provider-card .step-label {
      color: var(--color-copper);
    }

    .provider-card .detail-body {
      padding: 0 1rem 1rem;
    }

    .provider-card h3 {
      margin: 1.15rem 0 0.45rem;
    }

    .provider-card h3:first-child {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .provider-card .step-list {
      gap: 0.6rem;
    }

    .warning {
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 0.95rem 1rem;
      border-left: 5px solid var(--color-copper);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: rgba(143, 78, 36, 0.08);
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .provider-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
    }

    .provider-tile {
      padding: 0.9rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: var(--color-surface);
    }

    .provider-tile strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    }

    .provider-tile span {
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      body {
        padding: 0 0.9rem 3rem;
      }

      .site-header {
        margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
      }

      .provider-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      summary {
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      }

      .chevron {
        display: none;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="page">
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="site-name" href="/">Built with Jon</a>
      <a class="top-link" href="/ai-assistant/">AI Assistant hub</a>
      <a class="top-link" href="/ai-assistant/cowork/">Cowork DIY</a>
      <a class="top-link" href="/ai-assistant-workshop/">Guided class</a>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Technical DIY path</p>
        <h1>Set up the Claude Code personal assistant starter kit</h1>
        <p class="lede">Use this checklist if you want the file-based Claude Code version of the assistant. It is the more technical path: you install local tools, unzip a resource pack, and keep the assistant's memory in plain files you can inspect.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Related AI assistant paths">
          <a class="hero-action primary" href="#setup-steps">Start the setup checklist</a>
          <a class="hero-action" href="/ai-assistant/">Compare all paths</a>
          <a class="hero-action" href="/ai-assistant-workshop/">Get guided help</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="panel bring-panel" aria-labelledby="what-to-bring">
        <h2 id="what-to-bring">What this path requires</h2>
        <ul class="bring-list">
          <li><span class="check">1</span><span><strong>Claude Pro or Max subscription</strong></span></li>
          <li><span class="check">2</span><span><strong>Google account</strong></span></li>
          <li><span class="check">3</span><span><strong>Laptop</strong> with the Claude Desktop app installed and signed in</span></li>
          <li><span class="check">4</span><span><strong>Mobile phone</strong> with the Claude mobile app installed and signed in</span></li>
          <li><span class="check">5</span><span><strong>Git installed</strong> so Claude Code can work with local files and project history</span></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <p class="section-label">Setup steps</p>

      <section class="setup-stack" id="setup-steps" aria-label="Claude Code setup steps">
        <details class="panel" open>
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 1</span>
              <h2>Claude Pro or Max subscription</h2>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>Create or sign in to your Claude account.</strong> Go to <a href="https://claude.ai">claude.ai</a>.</li>
              <li><strong>Upgrade to Claude Pro or Max.</strong> Go to <a href="https://claude.ai/upgrade">claude.ai/upgrade</a>, choose Pro or Max, and complete checkout. Pro is enough to start.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="panel">
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 2</span>
              <h2>Install Claude Desktop on your laptop and sign in</h2>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>Download Claude Desktop.</strong> Go to <a href="https://claude.com/download">claude.com/download</a> and choose macOS or Windows.</li>
              <li><strong>Install and open it.</strong> On Mac, open Claude from Applications. On Windows, open Claude from the Start menu.</li>
              <li><strong>Sign in with the same Claude account.</strong> Send a quick hello message to confirm the app works.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="note">Claude Desktop supports macOS 11 or newer and Windows 10 or newer. If you are on a locked-down work laptop, install early in case your IT policy blocks new apps.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="panel">
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 3</span>
              <h2>Install Claude Mobile on your phone and sign in</h2>
              <p class="summary-desc">Use the same Claude account on mobile so your assistant is reachable from your phone.</p>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>Install Claude Mobile.</strong> Use the iOS App Store or Google Play links from <a href="https://claude.com/download">claude.com/download</a>.</li>
              <li><strong>Sign in with the same Claude account.</strong> Send a quick hello message from your phone.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="note">Claude Mobile is optional for the technical build, but useful when you want to check in from your phone.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="panel">
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 4</span>
              <h2>Set up the Google account your assistant can use</h2>
              <p class="summary-desc">Have a Google account ready, but do not connect sensitive mail or calendar data until you understand the permissions.</p>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <p><strong>If your primary email and calendar are Google, then you are done.</strong> Keep that login available for the assistant setup.</p>
            <p>If you use iCloud, Outlook, Yahoo, or another provider, create a free Google account at <a href="https://accounts.google.com/signup">accounts.google.com/signup</a>. Use it for starter exercises or for safe forwarding tests. You do not need to migrate your life into Google.</p>
            <p class="note">If your email or calendar lives in iCloud, Outlook, or Yahoo, keep the <a href="provider-setup.html">provider setup reference</a> handy for provider-specific forwarding or calendar steps.</p>

            <div class="privacy-callout" aria-labelledby="privacy-safety">
              <div class="privacy-heading">
                <span class="caution-icon" aria-hidden="true"><span>!</span></span>
                <h3 id="privacy-safety">Privacy &amp; safety before you connect anything</h3>
              </div>
              <ul class="safety-list">
                <li><strong>Do not connect Google, Gmail, or Calendar directly to Claude until you understand the permission scope</strong> unless you already did and are comfortable keeping it connected.</li>
                <li><strong>Read access can expose private content:</strong> emails, attachments, meeting details, file names, and documents.</li>
                <li><strong>Write access can change real things:</strong> agents may send mail, edit or delete files, create invites, reschedule meetings, or cancel events.</li>
                <li><strong>Use the smallest permission that works</strong> and revoke access after testing if you only needed it temporarily.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <p class="warning"><strong>Safety note:</strong> Do not forward a sensitive inbox or publish a sensitive calendar just to test. Use sample events or a dedicated Google account if you are unsure.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="panel">
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 5</span>
              <h2>Optional: prepare phone messaging</h2>
              <p class="summary-desc">Use this only if you want a phone path later. You can skip it for the first local setup.</p>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>iPhone users can use iMessage paths later.</strong> No additional messaging app is required for the first local setup.</li>
              <li><strong>Android users can use Telegram later.</strong> Install it from <a href="https://telegram.org/dl/android">telegram.org/dl/android</a>, then create or sign in to a Telegram account with your mobile phone number.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="note">Telegram accounts are tied to mobile phone numbers. Skip this unless you specifically want to experiment with a Telegram phone channel.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="panel">
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 6</span>
              <h2>Download the starter materials</h2>
              <p class="summary-desc">Grab the resource pack and unzip it to your Downloads folder.</p>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>Download the starter materials.</strong> Get the resource pack here: <a href="workshop-resource-pack.zip">workshop-resource-pack.zip</a>.</li>
              <li><strong>Unzip it to your Downloads folder.</strong> On Mac, double-click the <code>.zip</code> file. On Windows, right-click it and choose <strong>Extract All</strong>. Keeping the unzipped folder in <code>Downloads</code> makes the starter instructions easier to follow.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="note">The unzipped folder is still named <code>Workshop-Resource-Pack</code> because it came from the original live workshop materials.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="panel">
          <summary>
            <div>
              <span class="step-label">Step 7</span>
              <h2>Install Git</h2>
              <p class="summary-desc">A small tool Claude Code uses to work with local project files. Quick on both Mac and Windows.</p>
            </div>
            <svg class="chevron" width="18" height="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="detail-body">
            <h3>Mac</h3>
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>Open Terminal</strong> (press <code>Cmd</code>+<code>Space</code>, type <strong>Terminal</strong>, hit Enter).</li>
              <li><strong>Run:</strong> <code>xcode-select --install</code></li>
              <li><strong>A pop-up will appear.</strong> Click <strong>Install</strong> and follow the directions. When it finishes, Git is ready.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>Windows</h3>
            <ol class="step-list">
              <li><strong>Download the installer</strong> from <a href="https://git-scm.com/install">git-scm.com/install</a>.</li>
              <li><strong>Run the installer</strong> and accept the defaults through to the end.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="note">Not sure if you already have Git? That is fine. Running the step again does no harm.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
